I owned the vhs version of this movie.  In an effort to replace my few remaining vhs tapes with dvds I bought the dvd video version of El Noa Noa with the only expectation of having the picture quality match my vhs version (which was over 25 years old).  I was very suprised to find out the dvd video version picture quality did not even come close.  Unforturnately I sold my vhs version (for pennies at a local bookstore) prior to receiving my dvd.  I wish I had not done that!  Whatever you do, do not but this dvd not matter how low the price is.  It is not even worth the time and effort to return it.  The seller's service was excellent in the transaction but there should have been some indication of the picture quality of the dvd being sold.
